    • dNODEBUG

      public static final boolean dNODEBUG
      debugging: IASSERT is an internal assertion, i.e. a consistency check. if it fails we want to know where. UASSERT is a user assertion, i.e. if it fails a nice error message should be printed for the user. AASSERT is an arguments assertion, i.e. if it fails "bad argument(s)" is printed. DEBUGMSG just prints out a message
